<ProjectLayout
  badge="Competitive Robotics · October 2025"
  title="LARC 2025 — Tec de Monterrey. The Tracky Project."
  description="Built and raced a custom ESP32-C6 line-follower robot that recovers from 90° turns in milliseconds — engineered under real competition pressure at LARC 2025."
  coverImage="/portfolio/images/larc_arena.webp"
  coverAlt="Tracky robot racing at LARC 2025 arena, Tec de Monterrey"
  ogImage="https://alesso-24.github.io/portfolio/images/larc_arena.webp"
  meta={[
    { label: 'Role',     value: 'Hardware Lead & Software Co-Dev' },
    { label: 'Venue',    value: 'Tec de Monterrey, N.L., México' },
    { label: 'Event',    value: 'LARC 2025 — TIR Line Follower' },
    { label: 'Hardware', value: 'ESP32-C6 · IR Array · TB6612FNG' },
    { label: 'Software', value: 'C++ · PID Control · Python · BLE' },
  ]}
  githubHref="https://github.com/Alesso-24/Tracky"
>

  <blockquote class="pull-quote" data-reveal>
    <p>
      <span class="lang-en">"Real engineering under fire — where theoretical math meets physical reality, and your code either holds the line or crashes out."</span>
      <span class="lang-es">"Ingeniería real bajo presión — donde las matemáticas teóricas se encuentran con la realidad física, y tu código aguanta la línea o colapsa."</span>
    </p>
  </blockquote>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>
    <span class="lang-en">Watch Tracky Race.</span>
    <span class="lang-es">Mira correr a Tracky.</span>
  </h2>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    <span class="lang-en">One competition heat. A robot that has to think faster than the track curves. Watch the Inertial Recovery protocol activate on the 90° corners in real-time.</span>
    <span class="lang-es">Una eliminatoria. Un robot que debe pensar más rápido que las curvas del circuito. Observa el protocolo de Recuperación Inercial activarse en los giros de 90° en tiempo real.</span>
  </p>

  <div data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100" class="video-embed">
    <iframe
      src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/LlpaLHTaqiQ"
      title="Tracky LARC 2025 — Line Follower Race Demo"
      allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
      allowfullscreen loading="lazy"
    ></iframe>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>
    <span class="lang-en">The Competition.</span>
    <span class="lang-es">La Competencia.</span>
  </h2>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    <span class="lang-en">At the 25th Latin American Robotics Competition in Nuevo León, we faced top universities from across Latin America in the TIR Line Follower category. Every millisecond counted. Every heat was final.</span>
    <span class="lang-es">En la 25ª Competencia Latinoamericana de Robótica en Nuevo León, nos enfrentamos a las mejores universidades de América Latina en la categoría TIR Seguidor de Línea. Cada milisegundo contaba. Cada eliminatoria era definitiva.</span>
  </p>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100">
    <span class="lang-en">The environment was intense: fresh solder fumes, servo whines, teams pushing hardware to the limit. We debugged C++ memory leaks on the fly, fought BLE interference from neighboring robots, and constantly recalibrated IR sensors against the arena's shifting ambient light.</span>
    <span class="lang-es">El ambiente era intenso: humo de soldadura fresca, servos chillando, equipos empujando el hardware al límite. Depuramos fugas de memoria en C++ al vuelo, luchamos contra interferencias BLE de robots vecinos, y recalibramos constantemente los sensores IR contra la cambiante luz ambiental de la arena.</span>
  </p>

  <div data-reveal style="border-radius:18px; overflow:hidden; margin:clamp(28px,4vh,48px) 0; box-shadow:0 22px 50px -30px rgba(234,106,46,0.35);">
    <img src="/portfolio/images/larc_team.webp" alt="Alessandro y compañero en LARC 2025" loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%;height:auto;display:block;" />
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>
    <span class="lang-en">Engineering for Performance.</span>
    <span class="lang-es">Ingeniería para el Rendimiento.</span>
  </h2>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    <span class="lang-en">Tracky runs on the ESP32-C6 (RISC-V core), executing an RTOS-like control loop that guarantees microsecond response times — making the robot hunt the line instead of just following it.</span>
    <span class="lang-es">Tracky corre sobre el ESP32-C6 (núcleo RISC-V), ejecutando un bucle de control tipo RTOS que garantiza tiempos de respuesta en microsegundos — haciendo que el robot persiga la línea en vez de solo seguirla.</span>
  </p>

  <div class="tech-grid" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100">
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num" style="color:#ea6a2e;">01</div>
      <h3><span class="lang-en">Inertial Recovery</span><span class="lang-es">Recuperación Inercial</span></h3>
      <p><span class="lang-en">All 8 IR sensors hit white → Tracky extracts the derivative vector of its last known position and spins back aggressively. Zero freeze. Millisecond execution.</span><span class="lang-es">Los 8 sensores IR detectan blanco → Tracky extrae el vector derivado de su última posición conocida y gira de regreso agresivamente. Cero congelamiento. Ejecución en milisegundos.</span></p>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num" style="color:#ea6a2e;">02</div>
      <h3><span class="lang-en">Strat-Profiles</span><span class="lang-es">Perfiles Estratégicos</span></h3>
      <p><span class="lang-en">Physical DIP switches hot-swap between pre-calibrated PID profiles: Slow, Balanced, Aggressive, High-Damping. No reflashing between heats — ever.</span><span class="lang-es">Interruptores DIP físicos cambian entre perfiles PID pre-calibrados: Lento, Balanceado, Agresivo, Alta-Amortiguación. Sin reprogramar entre eliminatorias.</span></p>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num" style="color:#ea6a2e;">03</div>
      <h3><span class="lang-en">BLE Auto-Healing</span><span class="lang-es">Auto-Recuperación BLE</span></h3>
      <p><span class="lang-en">Python dashboard for live PID tuning over BLE. If arena interference drops the connection, the robot continues autonomously at last known parameters.</span><span class="lang-es">Dashboard Python para ajuste PID en vivo vía BLE. Si la interferencia de la arena corta la conexión, el robot continúa autónomamente con los últimos parámetros conocidos.</span></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div data-reveal style="border-radius:18px; overflow:hidden; margin:clamp(28px,4vh,48px) 0; box-shadow:0 24px 60px -30px rgba(37,64,192,0.35);">
    <img src="/portfolio/images/robot_full.webp" alt="Tracky — hardware completo" loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%;height:auto;display:block;" />
  </div>

  <div class="callout" data-reveal>
    <strong><span class="lang-en">Hardware highlights</span><span class="lang-es">Detalles del hardware</span></strong>
    <span class="lang-en">Upgraded motor drivers handle high-current burst maneuvers. A custom multiplexing circuit polls all 8 phototransistors at full speed, feeding the PID with millimeter-precise position data. The ESP32-C6 runs concurrent RTOS-like tasks — BLE telemetry, sensor polling, and kinematic math — without blocking the main control loop.</span>
    <span class="lang-es">Los drivers de motor mejorados manejan maniobras de corriente alta. Un circuito multiplexor personalizado consulta los 8 fototransistores a máxima velocidad, alimentando el PID con datos de posición precisos al milímetro. El ESP32-C6 ejecuta tareas RTOS concurrentes — telemetría BLE, lectura de sensores y cálculos cinemáticos — sin bloquear el bucle de control principal.</span>
  </div>

</ProjectLayout>
